Growth Will Be Hurt If Crisis Is Not Resolved, Subbarao Says

-- B y   A n u r a g   J o s h i
-- 
2011-09-24T07:24:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/growth-will-be-hurt-if-crisis-is-not-resolved-subbarao-says.html
Growth in emerging-market economies
will be “interrupted” if problems caused by the risks of a U.S.
recession and  Europe ’s sovereign-debt crisis are not resolved,
according to  India ’s central bank Governor Duvvuri Subbarao.  Subbarao was speaking at an International Monetary Fund
meeting in  Washington  yesterday. His speech was posted by the
 Reserve Bank  of India on its website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anurag Joshi in Mumbai at 
 ajoshi53@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jake Lloyd-Smith at 
 jlloydsmith@bloomberg.net  